Arusha. Longido District Commissioner Daniel Chongolo has ordered the arrest of the council treasurer, Esay Mbilu, over the alleged loss of Sh84.37 million paid out to ghost workers.Reports indicate that the money was paid to 41 people who, after checks, it transpired that they were not legitimate employees.Talking to The Citizen on Friday, Mr Chongolo said the district s peace and security council summoned the treasurer four times to explain the missing funds but he was elusive.District Executive Director Jumaa Mhina, said on Friday that his office had already received the DC s order, and the suspect had already been suspended.He said the District Council would not continue to tolerate people who tarnish the council s image as it has not been received clean audit report for three years now.